# Galata Design System — Code of Conduct

## Introduction

The Galata Design System is built and maintained by a community of designers,
engineers, and contributors working together to deliver high-quality,
accessible and consistent user interface foundations.  
To maintain a healthy, inclusive, and professional environment,
all contributors are expected to follow this Code of Conduct.

This document outlines our expectations for participant behavior as well as the
steps to report unacceptable conduct.

---

## Our Standards

We strive to create an environment where everyone feels welcome, respected,
and empowered to contribute.

### Expected behavior:

- Be respectful, inclusive, and supportive.
- Provide constructive feedback, not personal attacks.
- Use welcoming and inclusive language.
- Accept responsibility for your actions and their impact.
- Collaborate with empathy, transparency, and openness.
- Focus on what is best for the project and the community.

### Unacceptable behavior:

- Discrimination, harassment, or bullying in any form.
- Offensive or derogatory comments related to gender, identity, age, race,
  ethnicity, religion, disability, or profession.
- Threats of violence, stalking, or intimidation.
- Insults, trolling, or disruptive behavior.
- Sharing sensitive or confidential information without permission.
- Any behavior that violates company policies or legal regulations.

---

## Responsibilities of Maintainers

Project maintainers are responsible for:

- Clarifying and enforcing the Code of Conduct.
- Reviewing, editing, or rejecting contributions that violate this document.
- Taking fair, consistent corrective actions when misconduct occurs.
- Protecting contributors from harassment or abuse.

Maintainers have the right and obligation to remove or block
comments, commits, code, issues, or pull requests that violate this Code of Conduct.

---

## Reporting Violations

If you witness or experience behavior that violates this Code of Conduct:

1. Document any relevant details (screenshots, links, messages).
2. Report the incident privately to the Galata maintainers at:

`galata.design@example.com`

3. Your report will be handled confidentially and professionally.
4. Maintainers will review and take appropriate action as quickly as possible.

Retaliation against individuals who report violations is strictly prohibited.

---

## Enforcement

Violations of this Code of Conduct may result in actions such as:

- Formal warning
- Removal from specific tasks or responsibilities
- Temporary or permanent ban from participation
- Escalation to company HR or legal teams (where applicable)

The severity of the action will match the severity of the behavior.

---

## Scope

This Code of Conduct applies to all:

- Contributions to the Galata Design System
- Discussions and collaboration within Galata repositories
- Design documentation spaces
- Official communication channels
- Internal and external community interactions

Whether online or offline, these standards apply equally.

---

## Acknowledgements

This Code of Conduct is based on established industry standards and inspired by
documents from the Contributor Covenant, OpenJS Foundation, GitHub, and other
open-source communities.

---

## Commitment

By contributing to the Galata Design System, you agree to follow this
Code of Conduct and help us maintain a respectful, collaborative, and inclusive environment.

Thank you for being part of the Galata community.